HEADWORD: caboodle
<hw>ca*boo"dle</hw> <pr>(k⟦adot⟧*b⟦oomac⟧"d'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The whole collection; the entire quantity or number; -- usually in
the phrase <col><b>the whole caboodle</b></col> or <col><b>the whole kit
and caboodle</b></col>.</def> <mark>[Slang, U.S.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
